      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THE BANKER NZ (3) settled close to the pace and finished well but could only manage third last start over 1760m at this track, that effort coming on the back of a sound second at Leeton the run before. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Won't find this any harder and he can give this a mighty shake. GEOFFREY BEE (7) went back last start then made a long searching run to finish 5.5 metres from the winner in second at this track over 1760m, that effort following a good third at Temora the run prior. Drawn to enjoy a nice run, with luck possibly playing a role at some point. Meets a similar line up and he can figure in the finish. WEENEEDDREAMS (4) is in the mix following a respectable third at her most recent appearance over 1758m at Leeton. ROLL PLAY (8) is the next elect off a last-start win by 1.4 metres at this track over 1760m.",
